## Prerequisites

- Ruby 3.3+
- Bundler 2.x
- Docker and Docker Compose

## Local Development

### Quick Start

```bash
make start
```

This starts the full stack (PostgreSQL, Rails) via Docker Compose.

### Common Commands

```bash
make start       # Start all services
make stop        # Stop all services
make logs        # Follow all service logs
make bash        # Shell into the web container
make shell       # Open Rails console
make test        # Run test suite
make migrate     # Run database migrations
make seed        # Run database seeds
make setup-db    # Create, migrate, and seed database
make install     # Install Ruby dependencies
make lint        # Run RuboCop linter
make routes      # Show all routes
```

### Manual Setup (without Docker)

```bash
bundle install
cp .env.example .env
rails db:create
rails db:migrate
rails server
```

The app will be available at `http://localhost:3000`.

